JOHANNESBURG – Ford is recalling nearly 1,4 million vehicles in the US over steering wheel defects. The automaker says a steering wheel bolt could come loose, causing the steering wheel to potentially detach. READ: Ford SA CEO recalled to US Ford says it’s aware of at least two accidents and one injury that may have been caused by the problem. Affected models are the Ford Fusion and the Lincoln MKZ, assembled between 2014 and 2018. The carmaker is also recalling an additional 6,000 cars for a potential clutch pressure plate fracture that could pose a fire risk. eNCA